Documentation for TurboGopher is included inside the application.Select the Help item from the Gopher menu.You also should get a complete suite of Helper Applications whichare included with the TurboGopher distribution from boombox.micro.umn.edu.======      Converting your old Bookmark files      ======If you have not already saved the TurboGopher 1.0.x bookmarks inyour bookmark window to a file, select the bookmark window andchoose 'Save As a Bookmark File' from the File menu.  Now quit fromthe old TurboGopher and launch TurboGopher 2.0. Select Open fromthe File menu while holding down the Option key. You will be ableto select your old Bookmark file and it will be converted to thenew format. You'll have a chance to save in the new format.Remember, with TurboGopher 2.0 you can cut-copy and paste any gopheritems.If you encounter any bugs please use your built-in bookmark to the'TurboGopher Distribution' to verify you have the latest version beforereporting it.  Or just use the following URL:<URL:GOPHER://boombox.micro.umn.edu:70/11/gopher/Macintosh-TurboGopher%09%09+>Have fun...	- The Gopher Team	TurboGopher 2.0b2	November 18, 1994